Merge commits that contain messages from all the commits from the merging branch cause smartcommits to process twice. This has the side effect of having duplicate comments in a JIRA issue. 

Can we consider making that a configurable option? In other words, detect that the commit is a merge and not process smartcommits for it?

Addendum: as a possible workaround, if you update your merge scripts and change #comment to #nocomment, the commit will still be linked to the ticket, but not fire a notification or be added as a comment.

