Browser: FF32+

When adding a link to a file, e.g.:
{noformat}
[file:///C:\Windows\write.exe]
{noformat}
the resulting href (the actual link) has all backslashes removed, e.g.:
{noformat}
file:///C:Windowswrite.exe
{noformat}
When I manually convert all backslashes to slashes it works and FF can open the file (of course, this requires to use CAPS and create a policy in FF). But this is not practical as no one will manually exchange backslashes to slashes, especially in long links.

Jira should leave the link as it is, and not remove the backslashes.

Well, the cream on top would be if Jira would remove all " apostrophes. When you copy a link to a file in Windows and paste it, it looks like this:
{noformat}
"C:\Windows\write.exe"
{noformat}
So the most convenient way to make a link is to write
{noformat}
[file:/// and then paste the path text with apostrophes and close it with a ]
{noformat}
When Jira would remove the " and leave the \ backslashes intact the world would be a better place ;-)

